
README
Irene Bazaga - Portfolio Website

This is my personal portfolio website, showcasing my skills and experience as a web developer.

Getting Started
To clone and run this website locally, follow these steps:

Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/irebazaga/portfolio-website.git
Navigate to the repository directory:
cd portfolio-website
Install the dependencies:
npm install
Start the development server:
npm start
Open your browser and navigate to http://localhost:3000
Features
This website includes the following features:

A homepage with a brief introduction about myself and my skills
A work page with links to my projects
A contact page with my contact information
Deployment
This website is deployed to GitHub Pages using Netlify. To deploy the website, you will need to create a Netlify account and link your GitHub repository to Netlify.

Once you have linked your repository to Netlify, you can deploy the website by clicking the "Deploy with Netlify" button on your repository's GitHub page.

